### You recently became accredited by [Good Business Charter](https://goodbusinesscharter.com/). What did it take to get certified?

[Achieving GBC accreditation](https://octopass.eco/news/accredited-good-business-charter/) meant demonstrating our commitment to ten responsible business practices &mdash; from environmental action and ethical sourcing to employee wellbeing and fair pay. It’s a great fit with our mission and how we approach partnerships in the public and private sector.

### You initially started with a different domain name. [Why did you decide to switch to .eco](https://octopass.eco/news/website-domain-change-eco/)?

The .eco domain fits our vision perfectly. Octopass&reg; helps organisations modernise how they manage travel and parking &mdash; which goes hand in hand with sustainability.

We wanted our web address to reflect not just what we do, but what we stand for. As we grow, we want every part of our brand to reinforce our values: sustainability, transparency and creating tools that empower users and reduce environmental impact. Moving to .eco made that message loud and clear.

